		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Gameboy Color Colorized Games</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have been trying to determine which of the original Gameboy games the Gameboy Color supports by using custom palettes.  Not only do all of Nintendo's developed games have support, a few games from second or third parties also saw some support on the device.  I believe that all have some kind of Nintendo connection.  Since MESS supports using the officially and recently dumped Gameboy Color Boot ROM, I used it to identify what I believe are almost all the Gameboy games that use custom palettes on the Gameboy Color.  
<br />
<br />Since some of these games have multiple versions, I believe the Gameboy Color determines whether it supports a Gameboy game by checking the game's name in the cartridge header.  Since there are no human-readable ASCII strings in the dumped boot ROM, I would guess that the ROM generates a checksum and compares it with a table contained within it and if a match occurs, then it sets a custom palette.  I have counted 54 games with support, and at 2.25 bytes, there little likelihood that the actual game names could be stored within the ROM.  
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.fpgb.org/?page_id=17">http://www.fpgb.org/?page_id=17</a><!-- m --> contains all the information anyone would need to find out whether the GBC supports more than the 54 games I have discovered.  Here are the games I have found:
<br />
<br /><ul>Adventures of Lolo<br />Alleyway<br />Asteroids / Missile Command<br />Balloon Kid<br />Baseball<br />Battle Arena Toshinden<br />Defender / Joust<br />Donkey Kong<br />Donkey Kong Land<br />Donkey Kong Land 2: Diddy's Kong Quest<br />Donkey Kong Land 3<br />Dr. Mario<br />F-1 Race<br />For the Frog the Bell Tolls (Kaeruno Tameni)<br />Galaga / Galaxian<br />Gameboy Gallery<br />Gameboy Wars<br />Game &amp; Watch Gallery<br />Game &amp; Watch Gallery 2<br />Golf<br />James Bond 007<br />Kid Icarus â€“ Of Myths and Monsters<br />Killer Instinct<br />King of Fighters '95<br />Kirby's Block Ball<br />Kirby's Dream Land<br />Kirby's Dream Land 2<br />Kirby's Pinball Land<br />Kirby's Star Stacker<br />Mario's Picross<br />Mario's Picross 2<br />Metroid II: Return of Samus<br />Mole Mania<br />Nintendo World Cup<br />Play Action Football<br />Pocket Monsters Blue <br />Pocket Monsters Green<br />Pocket Monsters Red<br />Pocket Monsters Pikachu<br />Pokemon Blue<br />Pokemon Red<br />Qix<br />Radar Mission<br />Solar Striker<br />Space Invaders<br />Star Wars<br />Street Fighter II<br />Super Mario Land<br />Super Mario Land 2: 6 Golden Coins<br />Super R.C. Pro-Am Racing<br />Tennis<br />Tetris<br />Tetris 2<br />Tetris Attack<br />Tetris Blast<br />The Legend of Zelda: Link's Awakening<br />Top Rank Tennis<br />Vegas Stakes<br />Wario Land 2<br />Wario Land: Super Mario Land 3<br />Wave Race<br />X<br />Yakuman<br />Yoshi<br />Yoshi's Cookie<br /></ul>
<br />
<br />The Gameboy Camera also probably has a custom color scheme, but I have no way to test that.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
